The paper deals with face presentation attack detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and computer security (cs.CR). The proposed approach involves training client-specific classifiers using deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The use of subject-specific score distributions and decision threshold tuning also involves statistical learning and optimization techniques, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
